Package: miCCI
Title: Quality-Preserving Charlson Comorbidity Index Estimation Under Diagnosis Anonymisation
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Gaetan", "Kamdje Wabo", email = "gaetan.kamdjewabo@medma.uni-heidelberg.de",
           role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Piotr", "Sokolowski", role = "aut"),
    person("Fabian", "Siegel", role = "aut"))
Description: Five computational strategies for reconstructing the
    Charlson Comorbidity Index (CCI) from truncated (anonymised)
    ICD-10-GM codes. S1 deterministic interval, S2 single-pass
    probabilistic heuristic, S3 multiple imputation, S4 Bayesian
    Dirichlet prior median, and S5 (Meta Learner) a cross-validated
    Super Learner combining S1 to S4 via non-negative least squares
    (van der Laan, Polley & Hubbard 2007). Reference population
    frequencies from the German Federal Statistical Office
    (Destatis 23131-01). CCI mapping based on Quan et al. (2005).
